01:32.400 --> 01:34.595
So, what do you think of Sandy?

01:34.760 --> 01:38.230
Arguably the greatest southpaw
in the history of baseball.

01:39.120 --> 01:40.109
My Sandy.

01:40.840 --> 01:42.910
l don't know,
l've never seen her pitch.

01:44.800 --> 01:48.395
-But she sure can cook.
-Well, guess how we met.

01:49.000 --> 01:51.389
l suppose we can rule out
Dodger Stadium.

01:53.320 --> 01:54.514
ln cooking class.

01:55.520 --> 01:56.839
You've been taking a class?

01:57.000 --> 02:01.073
-Where do you think l go every Tuesday?
-You're not here on Tuesday nights?

02:02.080 --> 02:05.709
No, l'm in cooking class.
And guess who's the teacher?

02:05.880 --> 02:08.189
-Who?
-Sandy.

02:10.240 --> 02:11.229
Who's Sandy?

02:13.240 --> 02:14.309
That's Sandy.

02:16.480 --> 02:17.674
Great story.

02:18.720 --> 02:24.158
-Alan is my star pupil.
-And you are my star teacher.

02:25.800 --> 02:26.869
So cute.

02:27.440 --> 02:28.475
Yo.

02:30.360 --> 02:34.069
-Can l have some more bacon?
-Oh, in a jiff.

02:34.240 --> 02:39.030
My mother always said,
''A well-fed man is a happy man. ''

02:39.200 --> 02:43.352
Our mother always said, ''Here's
1 0 bucks for pizza, don't wait up. ''

02:44.600 --> 02:48.195
Oh, that reminds me, she called
and invited us for Christmas.

02:48.360 --> 02:50.237
-You told her yes, right?
-Absolutely.

02:50.400 --> 02:52.868
You and l were going
to spend Christmas together.

02:53.320 --> 02:54.639
We are.

02:54.800 --> 02:57.633
-But you're going to your mother's.
-What gave you that idea?

02:59.000 --> 03:01.195
You see, Sandy,
it's kind of a family tradition.

03:01.360 --> 03:04.397
Our mother invites us even though
she doesn't want us to come.

03:04.560 --> 03:07.028
We say yes
even though we don't wanna go.

03:07.200 --> 03:09.191
When we don't show,
though she's relieved. . .

03:09.360 --> 03:12.636
. . .she gets to complain
about what horrible children she has.

03:13.160 --> 03:15.116
lt's the perfect gift.

03:16.120 --> 03:19.396
Christmas is supposed to be about
spending time with your loved ones.

03:19.560 --> 03:21.915
Yeah, going to our mother's
would cut into that.

03:23.400 --> 03:27.234
Alan gets to spend it with his son and l
get to play Stuff the Stocking in Vegas. . .

03:27.400 --> 03:30.358
. . .with a couple
of saline-enhanced elves.

03:30.920 --> 03:33.832
Does this mean
that l'm finally going to meet your son?

03:34.240 --> 03:35.992
l guess it does.

03:36.160 --> 03:38.594
Gosh, l so hope he likes me.

03:38.760 --> 03:40.318
The way you cook. . .

03:40.480 --> 03:43.836
. . .the only problem is gonna be
keeping him from humping your leg.

03:45.000 --> 03:47.195
That's the sheets.

03:47.360 --> 03:50.875
lf you fold them while they're warm,
they don't wrinkle.

03:54.560 --> 03:56.630
Beauty, sex, cooking, laundry.

03:56.800 --> 03:59.234
Marriage, boredom, alimony, death.

03:59.400 --> 04:00.992
You are such a cynic.

04:01.160 --> 04:04.038
-And you are such a sap.
-How am l a sap?

04:04.200 --> 04:07.078
-Are you blind? She's a nester.
-What's that supposed to mean?

04:07.240 --> 04:09.800
She throws you some tail,
a couple of pieces of bacon. . .

04:09.960 --> 04:11.996
. . .and bibbidi-bobbidi-boo,
got a roommate.

04:13.560 --> 04:15.835
''Bibbidi-bobbidi-boo''?
lsn't that from Cinderella?

04:16.000 --> 04:18.036
You don't think
that bitch was a nester?

04:19.640 --> 04:23.599
Anyway, l find that a couple of drops
of lemon juice on the dryer sheet. . .

04:23.760 --> 04:25.716
. . .really freshens up the whole load.

04:25.880 --> 04:28.792
Really? l find that just a couple valiums
in my coffee. . .

04:28.960 --> 04:31.076
. . .keeps me from snapping necks.

04:35.960 --> 04:38.394
Well, hold this, please. . .

04:38.560 --> 04:43.190
. . .l'm just going to pop these on the bed
while they're still warm and toasty.

04:45.200 --> 04:49.318
So which one of you guys is slipping
the high hard one to Martha Stewart?

04:55.360 --> 04:57.999
Hey, Brandi. lt's Charlie Harper.

04:58.160 --> 04:59.957
l'm coming to Vegas for Christmas. . .

05:00.120 --> 05:04.033
. . .and was wondering if you and your
sister wanted to celebrate again.

05:04.200 --> 05:06.430
Harper.

05:08.160 --> 05:12.995
Oh, wait, it's possible that you
remember me as Dr. Philip Gonzalez.

05:13.920 --> 05:15.672
Right.

05:15.840 --> 05:18.718
Yeah, hola.

05:21.240 --> 05:24.198
Anyway, l'm sitting here making
vacation plans and l'm thinking:

05:24.360 --> 05:28.478
''Where better to commemorate the birth
of our lord than Caesar's Palace?''

05:29.680 --> 05:32.035
Hey, Charlie. Hungry?

05:32.200 --> 05:33.315
Hold on, Brandi.

05:33.480 --> 05:35.391
-Not really, but listen--
-Last chance.

05:35.560 --> 05:38.393
l'm gonna start dinner
so the kitchen's gonna be off limits.

05:38.560 --> 05:41.074
-But it's my kitchen.
-So?

05:41.560 --> 05:44.120
l just thought it was important
to point out.

05:44.600 --> 05:46.318
You're so cute.

05:48.400 --> 05:52.234
Look, Brandi, talk to your sister, work up
an estimate and l'll call you back.

05:54.600 --> 05:59.071
Oh, hi, Berta.
Oh, l've got a surprise for you.

05:59.240 --> 06:02.038
-A mini-blind brush.
-A what?

06:02.560 --> 06:04.710
l don't think Alan's blinds
have been dusted.

06:04.880 --> 06:07.348
Probably because
you didn't have the proper tool.

06:07.520 --> 06:09.909
Gee, thanks.

06:13.920 --> 06:15.319
-We gotta talk.
-l'm on it.

06:15.480 --> 06:17.710
You better be,
or else she's gonna be on it.

06:17.880 --> 06:20.394
Because now l have the proper tool.

06:24.080 --> 06:26.150
-Hey, listen.
-You had your chance, Charlie.

06:26.320 --> 06:30.154
-lf you're hungry, take a pudding cup.
-l don't want a pudding cup.

06:30.320 --> 06:34.393
-We need to establish ground rules.
-Oh, okay, l'm listening.

06:34.560 --> 06:37.552
Okay, well, first of all,
Berta's been with me for a long time.

06:37.720 --> 06:40.314
And what she lacks
in housekeeping skills. . .

06:40.480 --> 06:43.870
. . .she more than makes up for
in upper-body strength.

06:45.800 --> 06:46.789
What's that?

06:48.080 --> 06:50.150
-Rack of lamb.
-Really?

06:50.320 --> 06:52.151
-You're making that for us?
-Yep.

06:52.320 --> 06:55.517
With roasted baby potatoes
and caramelized carrots.

06:59.680 --> 07:02.069
Anyway, anyway.

07:02.240 --> 07:03.434
Ground rules.

07:03.600 --> 07:05.477
l wanna be supportive
of you and Alan--

07:05.640 --> 07:08.473
Sorry. One quick question.
Chocolate or raspberry soufflÃ©?

07:08.640 --> 07:12.030
-lt doesn't matter, the point is--
-l'll just make raspberry.

07:14.120 --> 07:15.917
Actually, l prefer chocolate.

07:16.080 --> 07:18.355
Chocolate it is.

07:18.520 --> 07:20.715
Now, why don't l mix you up
a little cocktail. . .

07:20.880 --> 07:24.668
-. . .and you can take a nap before dinner?
-A nap would be nice.

07:26.840 --> 07:28.398
Can l still have the pudding cup?

07:30.160 --> 07:32.754
Okay, but just one.

07:32.920 --> 07:35.434
l don't want you spoiling your appetite
before dinner.

07:37.200 --> 07:38.633
Thank you.

07:39.960 --> 07:41.439
Go on.

07:42.760 --> 07:44.239
-Well?
-Good news.

07:44.400 --> 07:45.913
We're having rack of lamb.

07:57.600 --> 07:58.794
Oh, no.

08:04.360 --> 08:06.874
l'm hungry. Where's Sandy?

08:07.040 --> 08:09.952
She went to get a honey-baked ham
for Christmas Eve dinner.

08:10.120 --> 08:12.475
Honey-baked ham.

08:13.160 --> 08:17.358
l find it a little ironic that despite your
warnings about her nesting instincts. . .

08:17.520 --> 08:19.750
. . .you haven't missed a single one
of her meals.

08:19.920 --> 08:22.480
Yeah, l'm a master of irony.

08:22.640 --> 08:26.110
-l thought you were going to Vegas.
-Oh, you'd like that, wouldn't you?

08:26.640 --> 08:28.949
Then you'd have the whole ham
to yourself.

08:30.520 --> 08:32.397
You should talk, Porky.

08:32.559 --> 08:34.278
Who took the lasagna
under the deck. . .

08:34.440 --> 08:36.590
. . .so we wouldn't see him eat it
all himself?

08:36.760 --> 08:39.638
Who made a meatloaf sandwich
by taking a slice of meatloaf. . .

08:39.799 --> 08:42.519
. . .and putting it between
two other slices of meatloaf?

08:44.640 --> 08:47.552
l am cutting down on carbs.

08:48.120 --> 08:49.872
Yeah, it's working for you.

08:51.400 --> 08:55.439
When's the last time you looked down
in the shower and saw your testicles?

08:55.600 --> 08:59.309
l don't need to see them.
l know they're there.

08:59.480 --> 09:02.552
And what about you?
What do you call this?

09:02.720 --> 09:04.233
Goodyear or Pirelli?

09:04.880 --> 09:07.599
This, my chunky friend,
is water weight.

09:07.760 --> 09:09.318
Water weight.

09:09.480 --> 09:11.152
lt's genetic. l retain water.

09:11.800 --> 09:16.157
You also retain German chocolate cake,
lamb stew and Belgian waffles.

09:19.000 --> 09:24.199
Hey, people who live in fat asses
shouldn't throw waffles.

09:24.360 --> 09:26.157
Don't talk about my ass.

09:26.320 --> 09:28.356
l am very self-conscious about my ass.

09:28.520 --> 09:30.192
l'm-- l'm sorry.

09:30.360 --> 09:35.559
l'm just lashing out
because l haven't eaten in 75 minutes.

09:35.720 --> 09:37.392
Want some of Sandy's
homemade fudge?

09:38.680 --> 09:39.999
Don't play with me, Alan.

09:41.640 --> 09:44.438
-You've got fudge up here?
-Close your eyes.

09:53.560 --> 09:54.549
Okay.

09:55.800 --> 09:56.994
Fudge.

09:59.600 --> 10:01.033
You know what would be great?

10:01.200 --> 10:03.668
Honey-baked fudge.

10:04.600 --> 10:06.192
Or. . .

10:06.360 --> 10:07.839
. . .fudge-covered ham.

10:13.760 --> 10:16.433
Well, l'm really happy we get
to spend Christmas together.

10:16.600 --> 10:18.670
We don't have to go
to your mom's, do we?

10:18.840 --> 10:20.910
Don't be silly.

10:21.600 --> 10:23.238
Hey, you hungry?

10:23.400 --> 10:27.154
-l could eat.
-Well, you're gonna.

10:27.320 --> 10:29.390
Can we order Chinese
like we did last year?

10:29.560 --> 10:32.597
No, this year we're gonna
do something a little more traditional.

10:32.760 --> 10:34.751
Deli?

10:34.920 --> 10:38.515
No, we're gonna have a real,
home-cooked Christmas dinner.

10:38.680 --> 10:40.796
Whose home?

10:40.960 --> 10:43.952
-Our home.
-How?

10:44.520 --> 10:49.036
Well, l am dating a lady who's
gonna make us a wonderful dinner.

10:49.480 --> 10:50.629
Oh, okay.

10:51.800 --> 10:53.552
Are you at all curious?

10:53.720 --> 10:55.278
Yeah, a little.

10:55.440 --> 10:58.796
Okay, you can ask me any question
and l'll try and answer it for you.

10:59.440 --> 11:01.078
What are we having?

11:01.240 --> 11:02.912
No, about the lady.

11:03.960 --> 11:05.552
No, not really.

11:05.720 --> 11:08.393
Well, l just want you to know
that l really like her. . .

11:08.560 --> 11:11.279
. . .and you're probably gonna
be seeing her a lot.

11:11.440 --> 11:13.078
Do l have to like her?

11:13.240 --> 11:17.153
-Well, of course not.
-Then l probably won't.

11:17.720 --> 11:19.119
Why would you say that?

11:19.600 --> 11:22.478
We're very different people, Dad.

11:23.800 --> 11:25.518
So true.

11:25.680 --> 11:28.353
ls she gonna be staying over?

11:29.080 --> 11:31.878
-Yes.
-Where is she gonna sleep?

11:32.040 --> 11:33.155
ln my room.

11:33.920 --> 11:35.399
Okay.

11:35.560 --> 11:39.189
Just remember, the walls are thin
and l'm impressionable.

11:47.960 --> 11:49.632
Hey, what are you doing out here?

11:50.440 --> 11:51.953
l thought l should prepare you.

11:52.400 --> 11:53.389
For what?

11:54.160 --> 11:55.957
Alan.

11:57.160 --> 11:58.912
Remember what l told you
about nesters?

11:59.080 --> 12:00.308
Yeah.

12:00.480 --> 12:04.155
Well, some are hummingbirds,
some are robins.

12:04.320 --> 12:06.880
But you, my friend. . .

12:15.480 --> 12:19.314
. . .you've got yourself a partridge
in a freaking pear tree.

12:23.800 --> 12:26.553
-Sandy did all this?
-Yep.

12:26.720 --> 12:29.393
l think it's cool.
lt's like an amusement park.

12:29.560 --> 12:33.155
Yeah, Six Flags
Over Crazy-Ass-Chick Land.

12:33.920 --> 12:36.070
