12:53.080 --> 12:54.149
l like her.

12:58.560 --> 13:00.994
Will you look at that?
They're bonding already.

13:01.160 --> 13:04.709
Alan, your kid would join the Taliban
if they made their own s'mores.

13:06.760 --> 13:09.672
-So when did she do all this decorating?
-Hard to say.

13:09.840 --> 13:13.992
-Everything was normal until lunchtime.
-Oh, l missed lunch.

13:14.160 --> 13:15.149
What did you have?

13:16.360 --> 13:19.352
She made me a bacon, lettuce
and tomato sandwich. . .

13:19.520 --> 13:22.193
. . .with garlic mayonnaise
on sourdough toast.

13:22.360 --> 13:25.238
Oh, damn.

13:25.720 --> 13:27.915
Anyway, after lunch l took
a little nap. . .

13:28.080 --> 13:32.119
. . .and woke up
in Santa's Village of the Damned.

13:32.760 --> 13:34.318
Why do you have to be so cynical?

13:34.480 --> 13:39.838
There is nothing wrong with decorating
your home to show a little holiday spirit.

13:40.200 --> 13:41.758
But it's not her home, is it?

13:42.240 --> 13:43.309
Well, no.

13:43.480 --> 13:47.155
-Whose home is it, Alan?
-Okay, fine, l will have a talk with her.

13:47.320 --> 13:49.197
-Hold it.
-What?

13:49.360 --> 13:51.396
After dinner, you nimrod.

13:58.480 --> 14:00.596
Anybody have room for another Ã©clair?

